title: For Sale:  Pietta M1860 Army +Extras
postcontent: I've got a Pietta M1860 army, about 80 balls, about 180 #11 caps, about 30 wads, a can of pyrodex pellets, a bottle of powder, and a full copper powder flask with a brass nozzle, and if you want, I can throw in some Crisco (as grease for sealing the chambers, preventing a chain fire, or as shortening for making some pretty good cookies, it's unopened)Here's some history, at one point, this gun was the most advanced handgun in the world, and is in the most powerful handgun caliber ever issued by the US Army, .44 Cap and Ball typically being the "Army Caliber" of the days. Originals are typically a couple thousand dollars, back in their day they cost $14 (todays equivilant of $500 or so) the Colt M1860s were standard issue until 1871 if I remember right, the M1871 being a centerfire gun. Many centerfire conversions are out there for the 1860 Army, and I probrobly would have done one if I had the tooling, this gun holds 6 shots, but people typically loaded 5 for safety reasons, this gun hasn't been shot much, since it needs a pin replaced, and I havn't gotten around to it yet. The wood is beautiful, and the color case hardening and bluing are beautiful too. It's stored in a climate controlled safe, and I think you're probrobly done hearing my ramblings, if you're interested, just contract me, this is a non ffl item. These guns are about $200-220 used, this one also comes with $150 or so worth of extras, so I'd say 300 is pretty fair, like I said, if you're interested, just contact me.
